place.name: BARMER
place.gazetteerText: BARMER, a parish in Docking district, Norfolk; 3 miles SSE of Stanhoe r. station, and 6 S by W of Burnham-Westgate. Post Town, Syderstone, under Fakenham. Acres, 890. Real property, £1,183. Pop., 62. Houses, 9. The living is a vicarage in the diocese of Norwich. Value, £5. Patron, T. Kearslake, Esq. The church is now used only as a burial-place. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
